  "prompt": "Logins: Can I file my income tax return late, i.e after 31-08-15?",
  "response": "Yes, you can file your income tax return late, but there are consequences:\n\n1. Late Filing Penalty:\n- If total income exceeds Rs. 5 lakhs, you'll pay a late filing fee of Rs. 5,000\n- If total income is less than Rs. 5 lakhs, the fee is Rs. 1,000\n\n2. Other Implications:\n- You cannot carry forward capital losses\n- Interest will be charged at 1% per month under Section 234A\n- You might face difficulties in claiming tax refunds\n- You may face scrutiny from income tax department\n\n3. Last Date for Late Filing:\n- Typically, you can file a belated return up to 31st March of the assessment year\n- For AY 2015-16, the final deadline would be 31st March 2016\n\n4. Recommendations:\n- File as soon as possible to minimize penalties\n- Ensure all necessary documents are ready\n- Consider professional help if needed\n\nNote: These details are based on tax rules applicable during that period. Current tax laws might have some variations.\n\nWould you like more specific advice about your tax filing?",
